HEADWORD: Loathful
<hw>Loath"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of
loathing; hating; abhorring.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Loathful</xex>
eyes.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Causing a feeling of loathing; disgusting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Above the reach of <qex>loathful</qex>, sinful lust.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loathing</ent>⟦br⟧
